data.text:
Today marks the anniversary for Heaven Can Wait, released June 28, 1978. Over the years Iâ€™ve been to a couple locations, most notably the main house.

At the recent request from the reader about Joeâ€™s house, I decided I should probably look for it. Although I didnâ€™t track it down yet, I did find some of his biking spots here, around 24936 Piuma Road in Malibu. Special thanks to fan John Whitt who was able to locate the house nearby at 24851 Piuma Road!

The first location should look familiar to horror fans as it was used in A Nightmare on Elm Street and A Nightmare on Elm Street 3: Dream Warriors. This is the Evergreen Cemetery in Los Angeles.

The rest of the locations on this page were all shot at the Filoli Estate, located at- 86 CaÃ±ada Road in Woodside, California. This was also used in The Game.
